On February 11, 2009, President Obama issued a statement expressing his gratitude to both Democrats and Republicans in Congress for reaching a compromise on the Recovery and Reinvestment Act. He highlighted that the act would save or create over 3.5 million jobs and help stimulate the economy. The President also mentioned that the CEO of Caterpillar, a major company, stated that they would be able to rehire employees if the act was passed. Additionally, the act would provide immediate tax relief to families and businesses, while also investing in healthcare, education, energy, and infrastructure. President Obama thanked House Democrats for initiating the process and commended members of both the House and Senate for their urgency in moving it forward.